Output must be strict JSON with this schema:
{
  "result": {
    "title": "string",
    "assignee": "exact participant display name",
    "due_on": "YYYY-MM-DD or ISO-8601 datetime or NONE",
    "description": "markdown string"
  }
}
Hard constraints:
- preserve intent and language
- respect the "Language rule" exactly:
  - if it says force a language, title and description must use that language,
  - otherwise keep the language detected in current title/description
- keep title short and action-oriented
- title and description must be rewritten as one coherent pair, not as two independent texts
- if the title is simplified, shortened, or narrowed, the description must be updated to match that same simplified scope
- the description must not repeat or preserve details that the rewritten title intentionally removed
- description must reformulate the work as an execution-oriented brief: clear action, expected outcome, and owner context when known
- prefer concise markdown with short sections or bullets when that helps readability, but avoid boilerplate filler
- description should make the operational objective explicit, not just restate background context
- never invent owners/dates/facts
- use Reference datetime and Reference timezone as the temporal baseline
- any inferred due date must stay in the future relative to today
- if the source mentions a month, weekday, or day number without a year, choose the next future occurrence, never a past one
- if the source mentions only a day number without a month, infer the next plausible future date from today
- if Current due date is not NONE and the source does not justify changing it, keep that same due date
- title and description must never contain template placeholders (no "{{ ... }}", "{% ... %}", or raw variable names)
- assignee MUST be one exact participant display name copied from the participants list
- NEVER output NONE for assignee
- if no explicit owner signal exists, assignee MUST equal the exact "Requested by" display name
- if current_description is "(No email body provided)" or has no actionable detail, do NOT invent context
- in no-body cases, description must be one short factual sentence max, without boilerplate sections
- if current_title contains extra wording, examples, hesitations, or duplicate detail, move only the useful supporting detail into description and keep title focused on the main action/outcome
